ExecDesc.value: ClamAV Encrypted PDF File Handling Memory Access Error

EngDesc.value: A memory access error exists in ClamAV antivirus. The vulnerability is due to a PDF key length computation error in "pdf.c" while parsing crafted encrypted PDF files. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by causing ClamAV to process a specially crafted PDF file. Successful exploitation would terminate the clamd service resulting in a denial of service condition.
